value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: gibberellin A25 + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 = gibberellin A13 + succinate + carbon dioxide.
Catalysis of the reaction: gibberellin A13 + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 = gibberellin A43 + succinate + carbon dioxide.
Catalysis of the reaction: gibberellin A25 + 2-oxoglutarate(2-) + O2 = gibberellin A46 + succinate(2-) + carbon dioxide.
Catalysis of the reaction: gibberellin A12 + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 = gibberellin A14 + succinate + carbon dioxide.
Catalysis of the reaction: gibberellin A17 + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 = gibberellin A28 + succinate + carbon dioxide.
Catalysis of the reaction: gibberellin A28 + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 = (2betaOH)-gibberellin28 + succinate + carbon dioxide.
Catalysis of the reaction: DIBOA-beta-D-glucoside + O2 + 2-oxoglutarate = TRIBOA-beta-D-glucoside + succinate + carbon dioxide.
Catalysis of the reaction: TRIBOA-beta-D-glucoside + S-adenosyl-L-methionine = (2R)-DIMBOA glucoside + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: acetyl-CoA + benzyl alcohol = benzyl acetate + CoA. Also converts (E)-cinnamyl alcohol into (E)-cinnamyl acetate.
Catalysis of the reaction: O2 + 2 an ubiquinol = 2 H2O + 2 an ubiquinone.
Catalysis of the reaction: H+ + 24-methyldesmosterol + NADPH = campesterol + NADP.
Catalysis of the reaction: (2R)-DIMBOA glucoside + H2O = H+ + DIMBOA + beta-D-glucose.
Catalysis of the reaction: campest-4-en-3beta-ol + NAD = campest-4-en-3-one + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: cathasterone + O2 + a reduced electron acceptor = teasterone + H2O + an oxidized electron acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction: 1D-myo-inositol 1,3,4,6-tetrakisphosphate + ATP = 1D-myo-inositol 1,2,3,4,6-pentakisphosphate + ADP + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: 1D-myo-inositol 1,2,3,4,6-pentakisphosphate + ATP = 1D-myo-inositol hexakisphosphate + ADP + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: typhasterol + O2 + a reduced electron acceptor = castasterone + H2O + an oxidized electron acceptor.

Catalysis of the reaction: castasterone + O2 + reduced [NADPH--hemoprotein reductase] = brassinolide + H+ + H2O + oxidized [NADPH--hemoprotein reductase]. Broad specificity for several brassinosteroids, including castasterone, teasterone, and typhasterol.
Catalysis of the reaction: benzoyl-CoA + 3 malonyl-CoA + 3 H+ = 2,4,6-trihydroxybenzophenone + 4 coenzyme A + 3 carbon dioxide.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2 H+ + 4-coumaryl-CoA + H2O + 3 malonyl-CoA = 4 coenzyme A + 3 carbon dioxide + p-coumaroyltriacetate.
Catalysis of the reaction: gibberellin A14 + O2 + 2-oxoglutarate = gibberellin A37 + carbon dioxide + succinate.
Catalysis of the reaction: gibberellin A36 + O2 + 2-oxoglutarate = H+ + gibberellin A4 + succinate + 2 carbon dioxide.
Catalysis of the reaction: 1,7-dimethylxanthine + S-adenosyl-L-methionine = H+ + caffeine + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine. Also converts theobromine to caffeine and 7-methylxanthine to theobromine.
Catalysis of the reaction: H+ + eriodictyol + NADPH + O2 = 2-(3,4-dihydroxyphenyl)-5-hydroxy-4-oxo-4H-chromen-7-olate luteolin-7-olate(1-) + NADP + 2 H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction: H+ + chlorophyllide a(1-) + 2-trans,6-trans,10-trans-geranylgeranyl diphosphate(3-) = geranylgeranyl-chlorophyll a + diphosphoric acid.
Catalysis of the reaction: H+ + chlorophyllide b(1-) + 2-trans,6-trans,10-trans-geranylgeranyl diphosphate = geranylgeranyl-chlorophyll b + diphosphoric acid.
Catalysis of the reaction: H+ + chlorophyllide b + (E)-3,7,11,15-tetramethylhexadec-2-en-1-yl diphosphate = chlorophyll b + diphosphoric acid.
Catalysis of the reaction: gibberellin A15 (closed lactone form) + O2 + 2-oxoglutarate = gibberellin A37 (closed lactone form) + succinate + carbon dioxide.
Catalysis of the reaction: NADPH + H2O = NADH + hydrogenphosphate.

Catalysis of the reaction: a very-long-chain 2,3-saturated fatty acyl-CoA + NADP+ = a very-long-chain (2E)-enoyl-CoA + H+ + NADPH. This reaction is the fourth (reduction) step of the four-step fatty acid elongation cycle in the endoplasmic reticulum that extends fatty acids of C-16 or longer with an additional 2-C unit.
Catalysis of the reaction: (S)-eriodictyol + S-adenosyl-L-methionine = (S)-homoeriodictyol + H+ + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine.
Catalysis of the reaction: eriodictyol + S-adenosyl-L-methionine = H+ + hesperetin(1-) + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine.
Catalysis of the reaction: a ribonucleoside 5'-triphosphate + phytyl phosphate = a ribonucleoside 5'-diphosphate + phytyl diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: 6-deoxotyphasterol + O2 + a reduced electron acceptor = 6-deoxocastasterone + H2O + an oxidized electron acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction: H+ + UDP-alpha-D-glucuronate = UDP-alpha-D-apiose + carbon dioxide.
Catalysis of the reaction: (S)-naringenin(1-) + S-adenosyl-L-methionine = sakuranetin + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: (S)-naringenin + S-adenosyl-L-methionine = 2 H+ + ponciretin + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine.
Catalysis of the reaction: flavan-3,3',4,4',5,5',7-heptol + O2 + 2-oxoglutarate = H+ + delphinidin + 2 H2O + carbon dioxide + succinate.
Catalysis of the reaction: an L-1-phosphatidyl-inositol + a dihydroceramide = an inositol phosphodihydroceramide + a 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol.
Catalysis of the reaction: an N-(1,2-saturated acyl)sphinganine + 2 Fe(II)-[cytochrome b5] + 2 H+ + O2 = an N-[(2'R)-hydroxyacyl]sphinganine + 2 Fe(III)-[cytochrome b5] + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction: a dihydroceramide + 2 Fe(II)-[cytochrome b5] + 2 H+ + O2 = a phytoceramide + 2 Fe(III)-[cytochrome b5] + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2 H+ + 4-coumaryl-CoA + 3 malonyl-CoA( = p-coumaroyltriacetic acid lactone + 4 coenzyme A + 3 carbon dioxide.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2 H+ + isovaleryl-CoA + 3 malonyl-CoA = 6-(4-methyl-2-oxopentyl)-4-hydroxy-2-pyrone + 4 coenzyme A + 3 carbon dioxide.
Catalysis of the reaction: cannabigerolate + O2 = delta(9)-tetrahydrocannabinolic acid + hydrogen peroxide.
Catalysis of the reaction: cannabigerolate + O2 = cannabidiolate + hydrogen peroxide.
Catalysis of the reaction: H+ + isofucosterol + O2 + NADPH = (22alpha)-hydroxy-isofucosterol + H2O + NADP.
Catalysis of the reaction: H+ + epidihydrocholesterin + O2 + NADPH = (22alpha)-hydroxy-cholestanol + H2O + NADP.
Catalysis of the reaction: violaxanthin + 2 O2 = 2 5,6-epoxy-3-hydroxy-9-apo-beta-caroten-9-one + 4,9-dimethyldodeca-2,4,6,8,10-pentaenedial.
Catalysis of the reaction: pelargonidin 3-O-beta-D-glucoside + caffeoyl-CoA = pelargonidin 3-O-beta-D-caffeoylglucoside + coenzyme A.
Catalysis of the reaction: 4-coumaryl-CoA + pelargonidin 3-O-beta-D-glucoside = pelargonidin 3-O-beta-D-p-coumaroylglucoside + coenzyme A.
